<TEXT>
Groupe des Assurances Nationales (GAN), one of France's three big
state-controlled insurance companies, sustained a slight decline in net
profits of 1.7 per cent to FFr2.32bn (Dollars 421m) in 1991, from FFr2.36bn
in 1990, writes Alice Rawsthorn.
GAN, which is preparing for a share sale probably later this year as part of
the French government's partial privatisation programme, is raising its
dividend by 9.3 per cent to FFr50.3, despite a drop in earnings per share to
