to FFr22bn.
Its net banking revenue rose by 10.6 per cent to FFr16.9bn. Last autumn GAN
announced its was increasing its majority stake in CIC from 56 to 80 per
cent.
Insurance, which is still the largest part of the group, mustered an
increase in turnover of 18.5 per cent to FFr39.7bn despite the competitive
state of the French insurance industry. However, GAN is believed to have had
difficulty in its UK and Italian insurance interests last year because of
the unstable state of the markets in those countries.
