<HEADLINE>
FT  28 APR 92 / UK Company News: IRH shares suspended
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PEGGY HOLLINGER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
TRADING in International Resort Holdings, the golf course and property
group, was suspended at 33p yesterday as the company announced that its net
asset value had 'seriously diminished'.
IRH, which warned in January that the profits outlook of the main
development division was uncertain, said the group had incurred losses for
the year to the end of March 1992.
Trading in the USM-quoted group will remain suspended pending clarification
of its financial position.
It is believed that the net asset value of IRH has fallen to less than half
the Pounds 5.6m called up share capital, prompting the Stock Exchange
announcement. At the end of March 1991 IRH had debt of about Pounds 13m and
assets valued at Pounds 16m.
The group has been in talks with its banker, Gamelstaden, which also holds
15 per cent of the equity. If a refinancing based on a debt for equity swap
or a rights issue cannot be agreed, then IRH faces administration or
receivership.
An extraordinary meeting is to be called to inform shareholders of the
options facing the group. An announcement is expected by the week-end.
