FT  28 APR 92 / Management (The Growing Business): Fund raisers rein back
their ambitions - In a Nutshell
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Venture capitalists have encountered tough conditions when trying to raise
new funds over the past year. Despite these difficulties, two venture firms
have made good progress with fund-raising though they have had to modify
their ambitions.
Phildrew Ventures raised Pounds 62m towards its target by its first closing
in mid-March and plans to complete fund-raising by the end of June. Phildrew
initially hoped to raise up to Pounds 150m for its third fund but is now
talking of a final target of around Pounds 100m.
Phoenix Fund Managers has raised Pounds 35.5m towards its first fund and
expects to reach its target of up to Pounds 50m (initial target up to Pounds
75m) within the next six months. Mitsubishi provided one third of the funds
with Pounds 14m coming from UK investors.
