fall in yarn sales also reflected the difficult market conditions in the UK.
Strenuous efforts were being made to control costs.
Turnover dropped to IPounds 48.3m (IPounds 55.2m) with an operating loss of
IPounds 1.33m (IPounds 255,000), and there was an exceptional loss of
IPounds 456,000 (IPounds 401,000) being mainly redundancy costs.
Loss per share amounted to 8.33p (6.09p).
