FT  25 APR 92 / International Company News: Kellogg helped by sale of unit
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NIKKI TAIT
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
KELLOGG, the US cereals group, reported after-tax profits of Dollars 196.2m
in the first three months of 1992, up from Dollars 163.1m in the same period
a year earlier.
Kellogg said the results included a one-off pre-tax gain of Dollars 58.5m
from the sale of Fearn International, a US food service subsidiary,
partially offset by a charge of Dollars 22.4m following the sale of its
convenience foods operations in Canada, and some other US assets.
Without these distorting factors, first-quarter profits would have improved
by 4.5 per cent. Sales were up by 6.6 per cent in the first three months, to
Dollars 1.51bn. Kellogg shares fell Dollars  1/8 to Dollars 56 1/8
yesterday.
